and for the &quot;if&quot;, I believe you are also correct, I think the &quot;if&quot; does have the choice of [EXPRESSION], which you can indeed use the greater than, lesser than, equal and greater than, and equal and lesser than, the proper symbols for them are:

addition: +
subtraction: -
multiplication: *
division: /
greater than: &gt;
lesser than: &lt;
greater than or equal to: &gt;=
lesser than or equal to: &lt;=
equal: =
not equal 1: &lt;&gt; (see the examples below on how it's used correctly)
not equal 1: examples: if (orc.dead &lt;&gt; true), if (game.x &lt;&gt; 5), etc.
not equal 2: not = (but see the examples below on how it's used correctly)
not equal 2: examples: if (not Object.Attribute = Value) { script } -&gt; if (not orc.dead = true), if (not game.x = 5), etc.

